# NexAI outstanding items (updated 2026-07-15)

## Resolved in code (verify in CI)
1. Certificate TOFU/renewal probe uses system-CA validated SecureSocket only (no permissive badCertificate pin write).
2. APK hash check is fail-closed in release; hashes read from release body and release-manifest.json.
3. Android CI fails when release signing secrets are missing; automatic release limited to main.
4. Cloud sync uses /sync/v2 + SyncCrypto; partial undecryptable snapshots refuse restore.
5. Password backups use passphrase + PBKDF2 + AES-256-GCM (legacy checksum backups still importable).
6. Offline login restores cached user or offline stub so isLoggedIn stays true with a token.
7. NetworkSecurity VPN detection reads Android native security snapshot.
8. Avatar network failures are non-fatal; UserAvatar + CrashReporter filters applied.
9. Backend client has explicit timeouts; request signing fails closed.
10. Crash reports redact Bearer / API key / sk- / AIza style secrets.

## Remaining / follow-ups
- Incremental encrypted sync (still full v2 snapshot upload).
- Split oversized UI/provider files (settings/auth/password/media pages).
- Expand tests for auth/passkey native channel contracts.
- Optional: provenance/SLSA for release artifacts.
